track_notes: Roadside parking. Walk up bridleway and take to the moor at around SC 344879 or a little before that. Often misty this summit.

A tarmac road eventually turns into a loose byeway to reach a col. Then a well defined path goes up to the summit. Return back to the col after the activation and walk down through Ballugh plantation back to the pub in Ballaugh. You can then use the former railway line trackbed to get back to Kirk Michael if you wish. There is an excellent bus service back to Douglas, Ramsey or anywhere else on the Island.
track_title: A day walk to include GD-002 from Kirk Michael
